ing evidence that `simple' and `complex'\nsuper-Eddington NLS1s can be unified within the same accretion flow scenario\nbut with different inclination angles. We also propose that these extreme NLS1s\ncould be the low-redshift analogs of weak emission-line quasars (WLQs).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 25 Jun 2017 15:24:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-09"}
